blog.name: dramaphan
blog.title: Yo I Comment On The Drama When Shit Hits The Fan
blog.description:
Phandom drama? It's more likely than you think.

.

My ask box is always open if you need a place to be dramatic, share theories, conspiracies, opinions, or general grievances. Fire away, my babies. Nothing is off limits. (Except for the things that are.)

.

Icon by phanniephobic, header by cinnamonnutlester

summary: 1/3 I mean, I'm not surprised that there is no personal connection.You can see that personal conection between Colleen and her...
question: 1/3 I mean, I'm not surprised that there is no personal connection.You can see that personal conection between Colleen and her audience and how much meeting her fans mean to her. Because she is one of the first youtubers who started doing it for fun and if she get hate it's because of Miranda not her personal life. Their audience has never been the best. They were two friends making videos for fun and everything we care about was whether they sleep with each other.
answer:
“2/3 And I know how fucked up it is even if the only person constantly asking if my best friend is my girlfriend is my mother. When I could say, as I’m not into girls and I think I’m not into boys either, that basically I don’t care. I can only imagine how they feel when the whole world is wondering about it and how much worse it’s if they really are together. And every time they got a little bit more personal or did sth differently, majority of phandom has focused it on their”

“3/ 3 relationship. Dan asked us not to focus on his depression and all people do during hiatus is focusing on his mental health, wondering if Phil is taking care of him or looking for proofs that they broke up. Sorry. Maybe what I’m trying to say is I don’t get it why people even are like that. Why this is happening at all. I could ship them, think they look cute together, I could think they are together but I would never dare to say it out loud on the Internet. It is not our business.”

…

Oh, I totally understand why Dan and Phil don’t give much to their audience. Because everything they have given in the past somehow gets twisted to be about how gay and in love they are. Nothing they say, or create, really gets taken seriously. And I can’t honestly figure out why that is. But I suspect it’s a case of “that’s how it’s always been.” New fans look at tumblr, or twitter, or whatever, and they see all these theories and conspiracies and assumptions being made, and they assume that because everyone else is doing it, that it’s okay and dnp must be fine with it. Phannies of old set up a culture in this fandom where it’s okay, and even encouraged, to be nosy, and invasive, and over-curious about Dan and Phil’s private lives. They set up a culture where it’s encouraged to archive every minute detail. Everything gets screenshotted and saved, right down to things as simple and mundane as what they liked on twitter or instagram. The Phannies of the olden day’s set this fandom up as a “detective based” fandom, and it’s a tradition that we just can’t seem to shake, even after all this time.

title: June 5: In Any World (Chapter Four)
body:
Explicit

Tags: Alternative Universes, universe hopping, friends to lovers, fanfiction, getting together

Summary:  Returning home after his second world tour, Dan feels lost, bored, and without direction. But things are about to get much more exciting when, while reading fanfiction in the bath,  Dan slips, hits his head, and passes out. When he wakes up, it’s to a world that definitely isn’t the one he came from, especially because his best friend is in bed with him. And if he thinks that is strange, things are about to get a whole lot weirder.
